(3) The Registrar , or the High Court in the event of an appeal from a decision of the Registrar , in determining whether a trade mark is adapted to distinguish as aforesaid, may have regard to the extent to which— (a) the trade mark is inherently adapted to distinguish as aforesaid; and (b) by reason of the use of the trade mark or of any other circumstances, the trade mark is, in fact, adapted to distinguish as aforesaid.
