(3) Where the name of any trade mark agent has been removed from the register of trade mark agents under the provisions of subsection (1) or (2), his name shall not be restored to that register except by direction of the High Court which may further direct that such restoration shall be made either without fee or on payment of such fee as it may fix, and the Registrar shall restore the name accordingly. [As amended by G.N. No. 186 of 1964 and Act No. 17 of 1980 ]
